commitmessage: Tensor permissions (#4014)  * Update duet notebook  * Add dev guidance to node.py  * Reorganize imports  * Begin refactor of message signatures  I should have commit before this. My apologies. Still learning the habit.  In this commit I created subclasses of SyftMessage for SignedMessage, SignedImmedaiteSyftMessageWithReply, SignedImmediateSyftMessageWithoutReply, and SignedEventualSyftMessageWtihoutReply and began installing them throughout the codebase (mostly just changing type checking).  I also discovered that in order to test things properly I need to be able to serialize and deserialize ReprMessage (so i can use it for testing) because we're signing the serialized form of messages (not the python, determined hash).  As of this commit, I have finished the ReprMessage serde, installed the new types and am about to continue installing signing by default into Node and Client classes. Then I will test.  * Signing ReprMessage works automatically  * Black src  * Init permissions decorator and populate services  * Init decoratorfile  * Install decorator across services codebase  * Add VerifyKey to all Action.execute_action() methods  * Basic tensor permissions now exist  * Create test for tensor permissions  * Update  * Rabbit hole of Possible wrong turns (#4005)  * Correcting coding terminology  * Fixed SignedMessage tests  - Removed old hello_root.proto - Turned off isort for now  * 🐇🕳 Rabbit hole of Possible wrong turns 😱  Tried to follow a thread from a ball of yarn down a hole somewhere deep trying to fix the node_test and the auth by serializing all the things. I reached a loop somewhere inside the ChildNodeLifecycleService.  RegisterChildNodeMessage -> Node -> Routes -> Connections -> ServerConnection -> Node 💥  * Fix flake/style errors  * Fixed some key and address problems  * Fixed key issue  * update protobuf  * Found issue with Serialization and Reference Mediated Callbacks (#4011)  * Found issue with Serialization and Reference Mediated Callbacks  -> Changed dunder __eq__ to accept Any otherwise syft_decorator fails -> Commented out unused All() -> Added safer vm, device, domain, network getters for ID -> Moved @property address up to Address class -> Found bottom of rabbit hole and added # WARNING comments at issues -> Black and Flake8 linting -> Fixed tests and added temp work around for HeritageUpdateMessage  * Fixed issue with MetaSerializable and Generics in python 3.6  * Added Work around for Serialization and Reference Mediated Callbacks  - Added in_memory_client_registry to AbstractNode & AbstractNodeClient - Not any different in practise to the earlier version passing refs - Added HeritageUpdateMessage proto - Cleaned up Message Forwarding Services - Fixed node tests, now they just need proper usage of auth keys  * Black tests  * merge  * Added helpful print messages to aid in debugging (#4019)  * Added helpful print messages to aid in debugging  - Added icon, name and pretty print property to many things - Added emoji converter to turn UID Hex into easily matchable Visual ID - WIP: Trying to debug node test using this new visual debugging output  * Fixed issues with node tests and flowing HeritageUpdateMessage back up  - Added more debugging commands to visually see whats happening - Added lookup_id to RegisterChildNodeMessage to ensure consistent key - Added verify_key emoji printing for easy visual matching  * Added separate code coverage step after Python Test Matrix  - This ensures that results of tests are run before failing on code cov - Yaml formatted  * Run black  * Cleanup imports  Co-authored-by: Madhava Jay <me@madhavajay.com>

commitmessage: docs: examples: or covid data by county: Add example  The example covers the following using the Python API.  - Writing a new model, wrapping fbprophet    - Overwriting a SimpleModel.__init__()    - Using joblib to save and load the fbprophet model class  - Creating Pandas DataFrames from DFFML Record objects  - Downloading dataset files with hash verification  - Loading data from files using the high level API  - Using multiple models. Model predictions will be used as feature data for   another model  Fixes: #947 Related: #945

commitmessage: [ENH] one-stop estimator validity checker (#1993)  This PR contains a `check_estimator` utility which calls all interface tests in `sktime` relevant to an estimator class or estimator instance. The class or instance in question need not be part of `sktime`.  This replaces the earlier, hacky prototype `check_estimator` which covered only `test_all_estimators`.  The new `check_estimator` uses the `QuickTester` class from #1987 and the forecaster test refactor in #1992 to collect test results via the universal `run_tests` interface.  Currently, only general tests and forecaster tests (if relevant) are called, but the pattern can be extended easily by inheritance from `QuickTester`.  This PR also introduces a *dependency change*: * `pytest` is added to the `binder` set of dependencies, since the `check_estimator` utility, which is showcased on some notebooks, now depends on `pytest`.
lsof_modifiedfiles: .github/workflows/test.yml, sktime/tests/test_all_estimators.py, sktime/utils/estimator_checks.py

commitmessage: Ast refactor (#4941)  * Ast refactor that includes: * property support + action for properties * static methods * ast refactor * globals support * settable properties  * removing props  * removing protobuf  * protobug changes  * reverting protobuf  * protoc changes  * Some fixes  * Added sy_serialize back for situations where serialize is taken  * Add copy method back  * Restored change to send method which requires tags, description  * More fixes  * Lib ast fix  * Type hint and tests fix  Signed-off-by: George-Cristian Muraru <murarugeorgec@gmail.com>  * Add util lost file  * Remove type hint  * docs  * removing protobuf  * proto removal  * mypy fixes  * pytest hack  * mypy fix  * skipping duet test  * fixing mypy err  * Disable python 3.9 tests because torchcsprng==0.1.4 not available yet  * Linting and small fixes  - Adding missing break to loopback=True _server_exchange - Renamed exception variable in logging to prevent shadowing - Added if not None check to Metaclass to satisfy linter - Replaced Logger code with template and added print=True kwarg - isort and pre_commit.sh checks  * Reverting back to python 3.6 compatible logging code  Co-authored-by: George Muraru <murarugeorgec@gmail.com> Co-authored-by: Madhava Jay <me@madhavajay.com>

commitmessage: [MNT] test for isolation of `pytest` (#4548)  Resolves https://github.com/sktime/sktime/issues/4544, i.e., testing that `pytest` is isolated in a plain `sktime` install (which does not have `pytest` as a declared core dependency).  The approach is as follows:  * addition of a new GHA job * only `sktime` plain is installed, no `dev` dependencies * a test file `_nopytest_tests` is added, which can contain `pytest`-free checks * currently, `all_estimators` plain is executed. As this crawls all modules (except tests and a few others), it will spot unisolated `pytest` imports, or imports of other packages. * further checks can be added later  Depends on https://github.com/sktime/sktime/pull/4551
lsof_modifiedfiles: .github/workflows/test.yml, sktime/_nopytest_tests.py

commitmessage: [ENH] MrSQM classifier - direct interface (#4337)  This PR adds a direct interface fo the MrSQM algorithm by @lnthach and @heerme, based on the `mrsqm` package on `pypi`. (fixes #4338)  This serves as a proof-of-concept for how we could interface estimators with cython dependencies, such as MrSEQL, also see https://github.com/sktime/sktime/issues/4296  Related to the feature importance question in https://github.com/sktime/sktime/issues/4336  Also adds a separate CI element which tests only the C dependent estimators, `test-cython-estimators` - this will allow addition of future cython estimators in external dependencies, leaving cython to the external dependency and isolating it from `sktime`.

commitmessage: Fixed issues with torch 1.5.x and 1.4.0 in test suite / op support (#4493)  * Updated CI tests to install torch first and added to allowlist tests  - Updated black to 20.8b1  * Fixed issues with torch==1.5.1 and missing isnan() tensor method  - Added torch==1.5.1 specific True division error for non float types  * Added support for torch==1.4.0  - Allowlist now supports Dict with additional metadata like min_version - Filtered division functions from allowlist for 1.4.0 that fail on int   Because the failure is a fatal error that crashes python. In future   versions of the allowlist we could specify certain data types for   certain ops to ensure as much testing as possible.  * Added more ops to test suite: 	- torch.Tensor.frac_ 	- torch.Tensor.reciprocal_ 	- torch.Tensor.transpose_  * Fixed "square" on torch==1.6 in python 3.6
